A total of 17 339 tests were conducted in the last 24hrs JOHANNESBURG - 3,232 new infections have been recorded in the last 24 hours. Gauteng is leading in terms of new infections with 980 cases. It's followed by KwaZulu-Natal with 797 infections. The Western Cape has 752 new cases. WATCH | The Western Cape's plan to tackle COVID-19 The rest of the provinces have under 500 cases. The positivity rate has dropped to 18.6 percent. Sadly, 87 people have died, taking the death toll to over 91,300.